Economic Freedom Fighters (EFF) deputy president Floyd Shivambu may well find himself in some hot water, after journalists captured his altercation with Media24’s Adrian de Kock outside Parliament earlier this morning. De Kock, along with other journalists, was waiting outside the building where Cape Town mayor Patricia de Lille’s disciplinary hearing is taking place. After approaching Shivambu and asking for comment, de Kock claims he was held by the neck and manhandled. This video via News24:  Hey Floyd, why are you so angry? Tomorrow is a public holiday, today is Fake Friday, KG Rabada’s suspension has been overturned and he can now destroy the Ozzies in the third and fourth tests. In short, life is good. When de Kock was approached by Times LIVE for comment, he said he would definitely be laying charges:  Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from 2oceansvibe.com. Click here to read the full text on the original website.